				 Whos who at IIM event

 A STAFF REPORTER
																								The best brains from the public and private sectors and the B-schools will come together at Indian Institute of Management Calcutta (IIMC) on Tuesday to pick the brains of a marketing guru. 
																								Professor Nirmalya Kumar, the director of the Centre for Marketing and the co-director of Aditya Birla India Centre at London Business School, will conduct a day-long workshop on Creating Customer Value through Innovation and Execution. The programme will constitute Guruspeak 2007, organised by the IIMC Alumni Association, along with The Telegraph. 
																								The series was started in 2004 to give professionals and students in Calcutta an opportunity to interact with experts in various management disciplines.
																								Kumar has a Ph.D in marketing from Northwestern University, Illinois, and has authored a number of books on marketing, including Marketing as Strategy. He is currently writing four books on global marketing and moving business markets beyond price to value. 
																								About the workshop, which has been divided into four segments, Kumar said: Its about finding the unarticulated and unexpressed latent needs of customers. 
																								The participants at the workshop  the whos who of Bengals business and industry  will get to see case presentations and hold interactive discussions on them, said Ashok Banerjee, the secretary of the alumni association.

